This paper deals with the problem of image restoration, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed algorithm involves the use of iterative support detection (ISD), which is a technique commonly used in sparse signal processing (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of nuclear norm regularization, which is a common technique in optimization and machine learning (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper involves matrix completion problems, which are often studied in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and multimedia (cs.MM).
